# Borderless Trips - Schengen Visa Interview Preparation Guide

This guide is designed to help you prepare for your upcoming Schengen Visa interview at the embassy or visa application center.

## 1. Common Interview Questions
Embassy officials want to understand your travel intentions, ties to your home country, and financial capability. Be ready to answer questions like:
- What is the purpose of your trip?
- Who is financing your trip?
- Why did you choose this specific country/destinations?
- Are you travelling with anyone?
- What ties do you have in your home country (e.g., job, university study, family, property)?
- How long will you be staying?

## 2. Key Preparation Tips
- **Be Truthful**: Ensure all your verbal answers match the documents you submitted in your visa checklist.
- **Be Concise**: Answer the specific question asked without over-explaining.
- **Dress Professionally**: Wear smart-casual or professional business attire to create a good impression.
- **Arrive Early**: Be at the center at least 15-20 minutes before your slot.
- **Carry Paper Copies**: Bring high-quality physical prints of all submitted files in a neat folder.

## 3. Checklist of Physical Documents to Carry
- [ ] Valid Passport (with at least 2 blank pages, valid for 3+ months post-trip)
- [ ] BRP Card (UK residency card)
- [ ] Signed Visa Application Form
- [ ] 2 Passport photos (conforming to Schengen standards)
- [ ] Confirmed Return Flight Ticket
- [ ] Confirmed Hotel/Accommodation bookings
- [ ] Travel Medical Insurance Certificate (minimum €30,000 cover)
- [ ] Last 3 months Bank Statements (signed or stamped by bank)
- [ ] Employer Reference Letter or Student Certificate
- [ ] Visa Fee Payment Receipt

For further assistance, reach out to our team via the Support Chat in your Borderless Trips portal.
Wishing you a successful application!
